The paper deals with generative adversarial networks (GANs) and their applications in image generation, image segmentation, and audio source separation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SD (Sound). The paper also involves the use of incomplete observations and the factorisation of joint data distribution, which suggests a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
